Want to build Apps for your customers, but you do not know deeply how to code, do not know how to use Xcode, and don't even have a Mac to build iOS? FluxBuilder Agency - White label version of the famous drag-and-drop FluxBuilder app builder. üèÜ FluxBuilder Agency creates Your Own App Builder, which helps you to auto-build your clients' apps or lets your clients auto-build their own apps by drag&drop easily.

Remove the old FluxBuilder. Install FluxBuilder 2.0 or later. Download Desktop version or https://web.fluxbuilder.com Open FluxBuilder, Sign Up an account for free, then Sign In. Next, go to Settings, select Agency‚Äôs AppBuilder: Select a plan to subscribe: When subscribe successfully, re-open FluxBuidler, go to Settings > Agency‚Äôs AppBuilder, you will see this screen on FluxBuilder: üèÜ Now you can setup your App Builder Name, Main Color. Select OPEN ADMIN to add information for customers, apps, etc. Go to the [Agency/Admin Guideline] part. Select OPEN to open Your App Builder - this is the app builder that your clients will login to design and build their apps. Go to the [Client Guideline] part.

The Admin Page is the page for Agency to work. To go to Admin page: On FluxBuilder, go to Settings, select Agency‚Äôs AppBuilder, and click OPEN ADMIN remarque Then Admin Page will display. Login with your FluxBuilder Account. You can save the link for quickly opening on a browser to get started. If the end of the link is ‚Äú/admin‚Äù, it is the Admin page. Without ‚Äú/admin‚Äù, it is the App Builder page. You can send this link for your clients. We also support to change domain to your brand.

The App Builder Page is the page for your Clients to work (It is Your Own App Builder). To go to App Builder page: On FluxBuilder, go to Settings, select Agency‚Äôs AppBuilder, and click OPEN remarque Then App Builder page will display. Login with the account that Agency creates on the Admin page. You can save the link for quickly opening on a browser to get started. Add ‚Äú/admin‚Äù to the end of the link to open the Admin page. Without ‚Äú/admin‚Äù, it is the App Builder page. You can send this link for your clients. We also support to change domain to your brand.

How to subscribe the FluxBuilder Agency plan? This is the guide to subscribe FluxBuilder Agency plan step by step https://fluxbuilder.com/agency Do I need to purchase FluxStore apps when using FluxBuilder Agency? For the Silver and Gold plans, you need to purchase FluxStore apps to activate the purchase code. For the best Diamond plan, you don‚Äôt need to purchase any apps. Can I cancel my FluxBuilder Agency plan at any time? Yes, you can cancel the FluxBuilder Agency Plan at any time. There are no refunds. Your own app builder still work normally until the end of your current billing cycle. You will not be locked out of any projects. Can I use My Own App Builder when the plan expires? When the period of your FluxBuilder Agency Plan expires, you can customize your own app builder, but you and your clients can not auto-build the app. Where do I post support tickets regarding FluxBuilder Agency issues? If getting issue, please post to our InspireUI support center https://support.inspireui.com (for Silver and Gold plans). If you are using the best Diamond plan, please email to support@inspireui.com

astuce This Build On Cloud feature helps you to build Apps for your clients on the Admin Page. Beside that, your clients can also build Apps on the App Builder Page. If you do not want this, disable Allow Customer to Submit Build option in Settings. (Steps: go to Settings ‚Üí Agency ‚Üí Advance Settings ‚Üí disable Allow Customer to Submit Build ‚Üí click Save). Agency manages all app builds from the Admin page. The Status of build will change after the process of build finish. Click the Build icon on each product to get started. The agency mainly focus on the Build Setting screen If you already add your own Git Repository, let Select Git Repository ‚Üí the app will be then built with your Git instead of the default source code of FluxStore app. Build Apps for customers (if needed) ‚Üí[Problem Internal Link]

astuce In this section, you can create accounts for your Clients, so that they can login to the Client Page to design and build app. You also can add or create products/apps for your clients. Create Customers Click Customer + Input Email, Name (required) and other information if needed Click Create Customer After creating, your clients will receive an email with their new account email and password. While using AppBuilder, clients can edit their information (except the registered email).

After creating a customer, agency can help them to create new products by one of the 2 ways below: Clicking on Product + button beside the Customer + Pointing on the customer and click + button. On the Product screen While creating product for customers, please check the USER EMAIL (required) to be correct. PURCHASE CODE: you can input the purchase code of FluxStore to activate the app. Make sure the Website URL is correct and connected successfully. You can upload your DESIGN CONFIG for the new product. Otherwise, the new app will display the design of the first templates in your created [Problem Internal Link] (or our default template in case there is no existing template). Run Troubleshoot to check your website. Click Create Product to finish. info To build Unlimited App - no need to input the purchase code anymore, experience with the Diamond Agency plan by emailing hi@inspireui.com to set a call.
Agency can remove any customer by pointing on that customer, and click the Delete button Click the View Product button to see and manage all the products of the selected customer.

astuce Besides building from default source code of FluxStore apps, Gold and Diamond Agencies can upload their customized FluxStore source code (their own Git Repositories) on the Admin page, so that their clients can auto-build apps for that source code. Obviously, your Git Repositories should be based on the FluxStore apps to make sure that apps are built successfully.
To get starting your Git Repository, you should push your new or existing code to GitHub. Refer to this Guide.

Follow the steps below to create your personal access token: Go to GitHub and login to your account In the upper right corner, click your Profile image, select Settings In the left sidebar, click <> Developer settings In the left sidebar, click Personal access tokens In case your GitHub dropdown some options for Personal access tokens, make sure to select Tokens (classic) Click Generate new token Input a short Note Select Expiration for your Git Select the scopes you'd like to grant this token. Recommend repo option Click Generate token Copy the generated token and save to your local

After pushing your code to GitHub, follow these steps to add your Git to the Admin Page: On Admin Page, login to your Agency account Go to Git Repository Click Add Git + Input all fields (required), then click Create Git. You can point on the ‚ìò to see the short description of the field.
astuce Your clients will receive emails from Your App Builder. Let‚Äôs change the email information into yours. (White-label, no more FluxBuilder or InspireUI‚Äôs information)

Configure this screen to display the Logo image and all the information in the bottom of the email including: Sender Name Sender Email Website URL Logo URL: show the Logo Image in the email Support Link: this link will navigate to your support page when user click on Go to our Support Center button in the email if the build is failed About: a short description about your business.

Sender Authentication is an optional configuration. In case agency do not edit the Sender Auth, the build result email will be sent to clients under the email noreply.appbuilder@gmail.com Agency can edit this screen to change the account in the email to their own. astuce Sender Auth require using SMTP Transport. SMTP is also the protocol used between different email hosts, so its truly universal. Almost every email delivery providers support SMTP based sending, even if they mainly push their API based sending. On this screen, agency is required to: Service: choose the Service of their email SMTP User: input the email SMTP Pass: input the SMTP password of their Service. To get the SMTP, agency should refer to their Service guide From: Input the Sender name with email as this format: sender name <email> attention Important Note: If the Sender Auth is invalid, there will be no email is sent to clients. Thus, it is important to Send a Mail to check the Sender Auth. After creating the Sender Auth successfully, you should send the first email to check if the email is sent successfully with the correct information: Click SEND A MAIL Input the recipient email, Subject and Content of the email Click Send Check the Response Open the receipt email in the Recipient email.

astuce The products created here are the showcase of your existing apps. Your users can open and change their design, except saving. Enable Product Settings in Settings to show products on the Dashboard screen of App Builder.

Click Product + to add a new product Product Title is required (ex: FluxStore Listing) You can add Description to give short interesting information lines about the app Under the App Type & Image, select the type of app according to avaiable FluxStore apps and upload your image for the app remarque The changes will display on the Preview screen on the right hand side. Now let upload the Design Config config_xx.json and Feature Config env.dart by clicking Update button Click Create Product info You can go to the Customer Dashboard screen to open the app to check how it work.

The created products can be edited and removed. Point on the product and click the Edit button or Delete button. You can sort out the products by clicking Filter and select any option to show products of the selected App Type. Select Refresh button next to Filter button to reload all Products

astuce In this section, you can configure all information for Your App Builder, such as: name, color, logo, show or hide blog, products on Dashboard, etc. After completing the Settings, scroll to the end of screen to click Save.
In this part, you will need to input the Agency Name to show on the AppBuilder. The Background Image is set to show on Login screen.

The Main Color will change all the color of all features available on your AppBuilder. Let select the color that show off your style and attract the users. The Logo is located beside the Agency Name. You can upload the 2 separate logos for Light Theme and Dark Theme Preview Logo is your wonderful logo which will display on the simulator as a Preview Layout while user configure the app design (before they upload their own logo). remarque Remember to upload your Preview Logo, otherwise, our FluxStore logo will display instead.

This Settings is for Products (on the left menu) In case you would like to present your existing stunning design apps on Customer Dashboard Screen, turn on Enable. If not, please disable it by turn off the option. Do not forget to input Label or you can ignore it if needed. Wrap Layout will help to display full of your Products on one page. If not, some products will be hidden and users need to scroll horizontally on the list to see the rest.
Manage the submitting Build action of user by Allow Customer to Submit Build option Send notification to users (displaying on Dashboard screen) by adding your Wordpress website URL to Notification.

As your experience with FluxStore apps, you will know Mstore API plugin which supports most of the app Features. To be more convenience when supporting your users, the Agency AppBuilder will export the Mtore API plugin under your Wordpress Extension. Input your Plugin Name ‚Üí click Save and click Generate Plugin to get it.

Add the Blogs/News of your Wordpress website on the Dashboard Screen of User Click Add + Input Name (label) and your Wordpress URL Select Layout: simple titleLeft Enable Skeleton to show skeleton while loading blogs on screen Click ADD remarque You can configure each existing blog by clicking the Edit button and remove it by clicking the Delete button
Instead of opening FluxBuilder to Cancel or manage your Subscription, you can open Billing to do that.
Click Cancel on Billing screen to discard the next payment. You will have access to your subscription until the end of the current billing cycle.
To change to another Subscription plan, please make sure that you have canceled the existing subscription package. After subscribe successfully, you need to reload the Admin page to see the change.

astuce In this section, you can import our UI Templates to show Templates on your app builder page, so that your clients can use them for their apps, as image below. Besides, Gold and Diamond Agencies can upload their own App UI templates on the Admin page to share them with their clients on the App Builder page.

attention Before importing, remember to go to Settings and upload your Preview Logo to change all of our logo images on these existing templates. Click Import Template button. In the list of existing templates, you can import by clicking on one or many templates (click and hold Ctrl / Command to select more). Click the bottom Import Template button to finish. remarque There is an Application tag on each existing template for you to actively select the correct one.

Available for Gold and Diamond Agencies. Click [Add Template +] button to add your new template. Input Title. When users click on the template, it will be displayed under the App Type. Select the Application: FluxStore, FluxNews, FluxListing. Upload the Cover Image to display a first Preview for users about the template. Upload Design Config config_xx.json in accordance with the Cover Image by clicking Update. Click Add Template + to finish. On App Builder Page, it will show like this.
After adding or importing templates, you can edit or remove them by pointing out the template and clicking on the displaying Edit button or Delete button.

image Build your own applications and publish them to the Google Play Store and Apple App Store to promote your business. With a regular license, you can build your app with Android Studio (or any code editor) and Flutter. Please export your configured Design and Features files, copy them to the source code of FluxStore app. Then go to this guide https://support.inspireui.com/, find your app name, select "Getting Started" to follow step by step. With an extended license or Premium subscription, you can use FluxBuilder to auto-build your apps. Windows users can also build iOS apps without using Mac (and publish them to TestFlight) with Build On Cloud

remarque Without making a purchase, you can view an app demo of your website using the drag&drop FluxBuilder App Builder. Afterward, you can build the test APK for free. Select Test APK or Test iOS to receive an email with your App Demo: astuce Please do not test the App's features on the simulator of FluxBuilder because of limitation of Flutter framework. attention Non-work features are NORMALLY because they require additional configuration (e.g. Map, Social Login, Push Notifications, Dynamic Link, Realtime chat, etc.). So if they don‚Äôt work on your App from Test APK or Test iOS, it is PROPERLY because they need to configure more.

Before building your app, you should finish these task options: attention Precondition: to save your configuration, please activate license with your purchase code of FluxStore or FluxNews apps (regular or extended licenses). astuce Issues and Solutions: If there is an issue when customize the Design or Features, please clear Cache by selecting Delete All in https://tppr.me/qU6l3

Input your Website URL, select your website Framework, input API Keys/Access Token (if any), then click Run Troubleshoot (if getting failed, please click Failed string to see the solution). - Make sure you input https instead of http - Make sure you do not input sub-folder domain like this [https://yaari.store/pk-en](https://yaari.store/pk-en) because it causes Rest API issue. Please change to subdomain or main domain. - Guides to get the [Magento‚Äôs access token](https://devdocs.magento.com/guides/v2.3/get-started/authentication/gs-authentication-token.html), [Shopify‚Äôs access token](https://shopify.dev/api/examples/storefront-api), [PrestaShop‚Äôs API Key](https://devdocs.prestashop-project.org/1.7/webservice/tutorials/creating-access/).
(you can skip this step) Enter PRODUCT LICENSE KEY (it is the purchase code of FluxStore Apps that you have bought). Click Create App.

If you see a failed message after clicking on Run Troubleshoot, please click on the failed button to view the solution. Alternatively, you can check the solutions listed below: Failed itemüö® Solution ‚úÖ Make sure you do not input sub-folder domain like this https://yaari.store/pk-en. Please change to subdomain or main domain Make sure you input https instead of http SSL Verification Please select Run Troubleshoot again or Ignore it. Permalink Setting Check your backend to see if it works https://your website/wp-json/wc/v2/products?consumer_key=your ck key&consumer_secret=your cs key CS & CK Authorization Please input your Consumer Key and Consumer Secret, following this guide. CS & CK Validation Make sure you have inputted the correct Consumer Key and Consumer Secret, , following this guide. WooCommerce Connectivity Your REST APIs are not enabled on your website, please follow this guide. PrestaShop Connectivity It could be missing the PrestaShop plugin/API on your site. Please follow this guide. Magento Connectivity You could install this extension to active the API integrate with the app following this guide. WCFM Connectivity Missing WCFM Rest API. Please install WCFM Rest API plugin to solve it. Dokan Connectivity Missing Dokan Rest API. Please install Dokan Rest API plugin to solve it. Opencart Connectivity You could install this extension to active the API integrate with the app following this guide. Listing Connectivity Your REST APIs are not enabled on your website, please follow Setup Rest API Shopify Connectivity Please insert "https://" before your website URL https://tppr.me/gJY9G Post Connectivity Please check if you install any strange plugins that needing the permission to access Cannot see my Products or my Categories (or slowly loading) To make the app load faster or to fix missing Product Images, you would resize images, optimize the network request for Images. For Wordpress Please setup the Regenerate Image plugin, then be sure your site plugin has regenerated thumbnail like this https://tppr.me/ckgYZ Firstly, go to Setting/ Media Settings, and set up the image sizes for the Product Image. This is our recommended settings - https://tppr.me/IbRvL Secondly, go to Tools/Regenerate Thumbnails and click the blue button Regenerate Thumbnails For All xx Attachements, then wait for the process to complete https://tppr.me/1fKLE To check if the image is generated correctly, go to Media and click to view any image files, select Regenerate and you can check the list of new images generated with xxx-smal or xxx-medium or xxx-large format https://tppr.me/1UpJj After running the Regenerate successfully, open lib/env.dart and update this value "kIsResizeImage": true, , or if you are using FluxBuilder, enable Image Optimization as https://tppr.me/PaFLh There is a good solution to optimize more image loading by converting the Image to Webp image type by using WebP Express plugin. This is also a good tool which is our recommendation to compress the images in order to optimize the image loading. For Shopify You can modify the width and height of images for high resolution. For example, set _imageWidth to 700 and _imageHeight is 1000 https://tppr.me/u24mx For Prestashop Go to Design > Image Settings, add list requirement images if it does not exist: small_default, medium_default, large_default. Then, tap the Regenerate thumbnails button: https://tppr.me/NO9VG :::tip If you see images have non-good resolution on [FluxBuilder](https://fluxbuilder.com/), don't worry, we downgrade the resolution of images to improve the speed of FluxBuilder. After building, the app loads images with high resolution smoothly on the real device. :::

documents.t: FluxBuilder is offered in both desktop and web versions, giving you flexibility in how you choose to use it.

Link to download: https://github.com/inspireui/fluxbuilder/releases To use FluxBuilder from InspireUI, ensure that your system is macOS (64-bit), Windows 10 or 11 (64-bit), or x86-64 based. The simulator on FluxBuilder only displays the app design, not its features. Therefore, please refrain from clicking to test features on the simulator. Instead, to test the features, please try the app demo.

Your system is macOS (64-bit). To install FluxBuilder, please follow these steps: Double-click on FluxBuilder_macOS.zip to unzip its contents. Right-click on FluxBuilder.pkg and select "Open" and then "Open" again. Click "Continue" until the "The installation was successful" message displays. Select Close and Move to Trash (or Keep) to delete (or keep) the FluxBuilder.pkg Press the Command and Space keys simultaneously to open Spotlight Search, then type "FluxBuilder" to run the FluxBuilder tool. Alternatively, you can find it in the Applications folder.

If your system is Windows 10 or 11 (64-bit), x86-64 based, follow these steps: Unzip the Fluxbuilder_windows.xxx file. Open the Release folder, double-click the Fluxbuilder_Setup file, and then select More Info. Click Run anyway and then click Next until FluxBuilder has been successfully installed.

If you are using an older version, follow the steps below to upgrade: Export your customized design and features by saving the env.dart and config JSON file. Delete the current FluxBuilder application from your PC or laptop. Install the latest version of FluxBuilder.
FluxBuilder Web version: https://web.fluxbuilder.com You can use the web version of FluxBuilder on any operating system, including Windows, Mac, and Linux, to customize your apps.

Failed to install on Mac: Right-click on FluxBuilder.pkg > select Open > Open again. It will work. FluxBuilder may start and then immediately close on Windows. To resolve this issue, ensure that your system is running Windows 10 or 11 (64-bit) on an x86-64 based processor. Then, try one of the following solutions: Solution 1 Open Run (by pressing Window + R) Enter this: %appdata% Delete the folder com.inspireui.fluxbuilder inside there to clear FluxBuilder settings. Solution 2 Please install the Webview library shown in this image. If you are still unable to open FluxBuilder, please follow these steps: Open Windows Update Settings > Click on the left menu. Tap to Additional Troubleshooters > Tap to Program Compatibility Troubleshooter > Click Run the troubleshooter. In new window, choose FluxBuilder > Next > Try recommended settings > Check and test program > Next > Yes > Close. Now you have resolved conflicts between FluxBuilder and other applications on your Windows. FluxBuilder shows error about VCRUNTIME140_1.dll file, check below solution: Go to www.google.com, search VCRUNTIME140_1.dll file, download that dll file and copy to C:\Window\system32, Restart Windows PC. FluxBuilder shows error about MSVCP140.dll, check below solution: To add the necessary file, download it from https://www.dll-files.com/msvcp140.dll.html. Once downloaded, add it to the FluxBuilder application folder (usually located in Program Files (x86)/InspireUI/FluxBuilder/fluxbuilder).

In case you already had your own .json or env.dart file (of FluxStore apps). And now you would like to change the app Design or Features. Just import it into the FluxBuilder tool to continue customization. Select Features > Import Data > Open JSON Design File > select your old config .json file (it usually is the lib/config/config_en.json file in your FluxStore source code) > UPDATE.

Precondition: Activate with your purchase code of FluxStore or FluxNews apps (regular or extended licenses). After designing your app via the FluxBuilder tool, you will export the customized design and feature files and save them to your FluxStore/FluxNews source code. The detailed guide.

documents.t: If you get ‚Äòfailed‚Äô result when Running TroubleShoot on FluxBuilder with your Magento website, follow the solution below: Copy Magento Extension plugin folder to app/code folder on your Magento server. Run this command in the website directory: php bin/magento setup:upgrade Clear the cache on Magento after upgrade: php bin/magento cache:flush Change the Store View code: In Admin Site, Move to Stores -> All Stores and click Store View to change the store code. The store code must be language code like: en, ar...

If you get ‚Äòfailed‚Äô result when Running TroubleShoot on FluxBuilder with your Opencart website, follow the solution below: Open the admin panel, then click Extensions->Installer and upload this Opencart Extension file.

If you get ‚Äòfailed‚Äô result when Running TroubleShoot on FluxBuilder with your PrestaShop website, follow the solution below: Install Prestashop Custom API Go to Dashboard > Modules > Module Manager > Upload a module. Select the module ‚ÄòPrestashopAPI.zip‚Äô. Create a new webservice keyGo to Dashboard > Advanced > Webservice > Add a new webservice key. Generate your key and select permissions. Click the Save button after finishing the settingsThere is a list of required permissions with the method GET: categories, products, product, product_options, product_option_values, languages, attribute, countries, shipping, payment, order_states, addresses, orders, register, signin, countries, states, order_histories, address, cart_rules Enable WebserviceBy default, the webservice feature is disabled on PrestaShop and needs to be switched on before the first use. Go to Dashboard > Advanced > Webservice. Choose ‚ÄúYes‚Äù for the ‚ÄúEnable PrestaShop Webservice‚Äù option and click the Save button

After launching FluxBuilder, sign up for a new account and login: Select Login as the image below. Then choose Sign Up. Input your name, email, and new password, then select Sign Up. Check your mailbox/spam/ads for the activation email, activate it. If you do not receive any email, on FluxBuilder please select Forgot Password, you will receive an email to reset it. Then Login to FluxBuilder. Issues and Solutions: If nothing displays when you're typing, please change to English keyboard (typing in English)

Instant Delivery: Configurations will be pushed on Cloud Storage or website hosting when published, without re-submitting to Google Play or App Store.
